    {
        'number': [70],
        'name': _("""Heroic Ships"""),
        'cancel_card': False,
        'mission': False,
        'value': [5, 3],
        'effect': [
            _("""Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. Select one of the ships listed on the card title (a single ship, not a Group). It is <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span> for the rest of the game. <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span> ships get +1 to their Attack and Defense. They also take one more hit to destroy (this is cumulative with the <i>Legendary</i> bonus; 37.0). They do not pay maintenance. <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span> status is lost if the ship is captured or destroyed. Instead of using a number counter under the ship, use one of the <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span> counters with a star on it. If the ship ever gets flipped face down again, it will look like any other ship. In the very rare case where a player may have 2 <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span> ships of the same type in the same hex, they may flip the <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span> counter to the 2-star side."""),
            _("""[b]When playing with Crew Cards ([12.0]), these Resource Cards cannot be used to make ships <span class="text-uppercase">Heroic</span>. Instead, they can be played at any time to draw 2 Crew Cards and keep 1. They may be immediately assigned or assigned during the next Econ Phase.[/b]"""),
        ],
        'flavor_text': _("""<i>"There will always be a Rodger Young in the Federation fleet."</i> Inspired by Admiral Ernest J. King who stated that <i>"There’ll always be an England in the United States Navy."</i> This was in response to DE-635 USS England’s sinking six Japanese Submarines between 18-27 May 1944."""),
        'replicator_effect': _("""Play this card to build an extra Hull on the Replicator Homeworld. Only one of these cards may be played at the start of an  economic Phase. This card may be combined with buying an extra Hull and with the <span class="text-uppercase">Replicator Capitol [g][#65][/g]</span> Empire Advantage so that up to 4 Hulls could theoretically be produced in one Economic Phase. Since it only takes three ships of Hull Size 1 to build a Type XIII or Type XV, in this extreme case the Replicator could theoretically build a Type XIII or XV AND another Hull Size 1 ship."""),
        'type': 'resource',
    },
